 &HT;    Best hits for shopping on the Web
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   www.altrec.com _ For the active, rock-climbing, trail-hiking,
terrain-craving shopper, there is Altrec.com, which specializes in
travel and sports gear. The site, which includes forums, travel
tips and live online customer service during business hours, is a
great place to start buying for your adventure.
</P>
<P>
   MUST BUY: Petzl Zoom Headlamp, $33.95 plus 99 cents for
shipping.
</P>
<P>
   www.topbulb.com _ Reading this in the dark because you're too
</P>
<P>
   lazy to buy a new light bulb? Find your mouse in the gloom and
get to topbulb.com. With hard-to-find bulbs for items such as
projectors, floodlights, medical equipment, automobiles and the
usual flashlight, fixture and nightlights, it's the place to go for
quick illumination.
</P>
<P>
   MUST BUY: Any purchase on the site gets you a free GE
directional night light.
</P>
