<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ Not everyone shares my
enthusiasm for the Florida Legislature. But I look on the first
Tuesday after the first Monday of March as something of a holiday.
It kicks off a two-month period when the state's editorial writers
and columnists may open their newspapers each morning confident
that outrages and comedy will leap from the pages. (Lane, Daytona
Beach News-Journal) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Losing weight is simple, yet
Americans spend $50 billion a year on weight-loss programs. Every
year Americans get fatter. (Rowland Nethaway is senior editor of
the Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
