</P>
<P>
   STAGE-BRODERICK (New York) _ By Matthew Broderick chats about
his pre-Broadway tryout of Elaine May's comedy ``Taller Than a
Dwarf.'' By Joan Anderman. 1540 words.
</P>
<P>
   STAGE-HIRSCH (Undated) _ The touring production of ``Art,''
starring Judd Hirsch, has been playing to critical accolades and
full houses in cities all over the United States. By Maureen
Dezell. 1300 words.
</P>
<P>
   STAGE-GRAY (Undated) _ Since ``Swimming to Cambodia'' in 1985,
Spalding Gray's monologues have been one of the highlights of the
theater season. By Ed Siegel. 1850 words.
</P>
<P>
   COMEDY-IZZARD (Undated) _ Rock comic Eddie Izzard chats about
his tough brand of humor. By Jim Sullivana.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PERSONAL FINANCE (f)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   INVESTING-INDEXING (Undated) _ Their champions call them
unexciting, but index funds are drawing lots of converts. By
Dolores Kong. 1850 words.
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE-COLUMN (Undated) _ More financial gurus have their own
Web sites. Some are pure publicity vehicles, but others have useful
information. By Dolores Kong. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   FINANCE-HOOKER (Undated) _ Couple has questions about their
portfolio balance and a mortgage they're thinking of prepaying. By
Kenneth Hooker.
</P>
<P>
   TRAUSCH-COLUMN (Boston) _ Breaking up with your accountant is
hard to do. By Susan Trausch. 770 words.
</P>
