<P>
   &UR; DEMONIZING HEZBOLLAH WON'T SAVE YOUR SOLDIERS, ISRAEL &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   To bomb the Hezbollah guerrillas fighting Israeli occupation or
just to threaten to bomb? That seems to be the only question the
Israeli government asks itself about Lebanon these days. As a
result, Lebanese civilians suffer much more at Israeli hands than
vice versa. True, Hezbollah used to be an alarmingly active
terrorist group. But nowadays, things are not quite so simple.
Indeed, for all the talk of Lebanese terrorism, it is Hezbollah
that has looked the more disciplined force of late, and Israel that
has been making innocents suffer. &QL;
</P>
