   &UR; `POSTER BOY' ELIAN BACKFIRES ON CUBAN-AMERICAN HARD-LINERS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Three months after Elian Gonzalez, a six-year-old Cuban boy, was
rescued from the sea off Miami, his story resembles the fanciful
tele-novelas that Latinos love to watch. Call it ``The Curse of
Elian.'' But there is also a growing sense that the story is not
playing out in the way that Miami's hard-line Cuban-American
leaders had intended. Ironically, they may in fact be helping the
very man they detest: Fidel Castro. &QL;
