<P>
   &UR; THE INTERNET IS RUNNING OUT OF ADDRESSES &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   On the Internet, naming your start-up can be more arduous than
financing it. This is because most Internet addresses, known as
domain names, have been taken already. In the .com domain, the most
desirable online real estate, almost every recognizable name has
been claimed. Much is at state. If the name space of the Internet
cannot grow, e-commerce will suffer. &QL;
</P>
