</P>
<P>
   Willie Whitelaw, a British Tory grandee, once accused Labor
activists of going around the country ``stirring up apathy.'' That
has often seemed to be the essence of Bradley's campaign. He is
such a laconic speaker that one wonders whether the candidate or
the audience will fall asleep first. How did this former basketball
star and Senate veteran turn out to be such a dismal candidate? &QL;
