<P>
   &UR; MUDDLE IN THE JUNGLE: U.S. NARCS VS. COLOMBIA'S FARC &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   It is not Vietnam, nor will it become so. But once again the
United States is preparing to commit lots of cash, military
hardware and advisers to a battle in a foreign jungle. This one is
in southern Colombia, where an embattled president faces daunting
problems, including left-wing guerrillas, right-wing paramilitaries
and the world's largest source of coca, the raw material for
cocaine. &QL;
</P>
