<P>
   &UR; SLICK OPERATOR: PHOTO MOGUL GETTY TOPS GATES'S CORBIS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   It's the clash of the titans. Both young moguls, both cornering
the world market in photo archives, both now based in Seattle: Mark
Getty, grandson of oil magnate J.P. Getty, and Bill Gates, who
needs no introduction whatsoever. This week, with its 14th large
acquisition in five years, Getty Images increased its photo library
holdings to around 70 million images. That tops its main
competitor, Gates's Corbis, which has 65 million images. As Getty
says, ``Intellectual property is the oil of the 21st century.'' &QL;
</P>
