   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BRUNEI-CHANGE (Bandar Seri begawan, Brunei) _ Things are going
downhill in Brunei, the tiny principality on Borneo that has been
awash in oil money since the 1970s. By Indira A.R. Lakshmanan. 1500
words.
</P>
<P>
   FOREIGN-JOURNAL (Paris) _ For the French, the affair with the
oyster may be at an end. By Kevin Cullen. 730 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS (p) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS-CENTURY (New York) _ Across the Empire State are the
hops of the most astonishing ethnic ale ever brewed _ the raw
materials of an astonishing, and raw, political culture. David M.
Shribman. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-CATHOLICS (New York) _ When Roman Catholics vote in the
primaries primaries, they will redraw a political dynamic
Republicans don't much like to discuss: the persistent unease
between the party's Catholic and evangelical Christian factions. By
John A. Farrell. 1450 words.
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-DRUGS (Washington) _ America's war on drugs, poised to
receive yet another huge boost in funds, is missing in action in
the presidential campaign. By John Donnelly. 1230 words.
</P>
<P>
   MCCAIN-CHARACTER (Tempe, Ariz.) _ Forget the cocky fighter pilot
and prickly politician, friends say. What really marks John
