<HEADLINE>
DVD SHARPENS JOHN FORD CLASSIC; STILL GOOFY AFTER YEARS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``How Green Was My Valley'' (DVD) _ Walter
Pidgeon, Maureen O'Hara, and Roddy McDowall star in John Ford's
1941 heartfelt dramatic story of a family of Welsh coal miners. On
DVD, the black-and-white imagery is sharp and bright, giving new
life to a wonderful old picture.
</P>
<P>
   ``An Extremely Goofy Movie'' (DVD) _ It's all in the title.
Goofy, who first appeared as a minor character for Disney in 1932,
was twice nominated for Oscars in the animated-short category, with
``How To Play Football'' (1944) and ``Aquamania'' (1961). While
it's unlikely he'll win an Academy Award for this one, he's as
limber and funny as ever.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Bone Collector'' _ Denzel Washington stars in this violent
tale of serial murders. Not a new idea, but Washington is excellent
as a quadriplegic detective. Not for the faint of heart: Some of
the killings are quite graphic.
</P>
<P>
   ``Never Cry Wolf'' _ Carroll Ballard, the great cinematographer,
made his directing debut with this magnificent adaptation of Farley
Mowatt's nonfiction story of wolves in the wild. Charles Martin
Smith gives a courageous and compelling performance. But the mice
he eats aren't real.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: March 14: ``Outside Providence,''
``Guinevere,'' ``Murder She Purred,'' ``The Architecture of Doom''
(DVD), ``Drive Me Crazy,'' ``The Love Bug,'' ``Bandits'' (DVD),
``Scooby-Doo Meets the Boo Brothers,'' ``Diary of Lust,'' ``The
Prophecy 3.'' March 21: ``Jakob the Liar'' (American version; on
DVD), ``Pokemon: The First Movie,'' ``The Limey,'' ``Endurance,''
``Whiteboyz,'' ``Horror Express'' (DVD), ``Velocity Trap'' (DVD),
``Swing.'' March 28: ``The Sixth Sense,'' ``Crazy in Alabama,''
``Joseph and the Amazing Technicolor Dreamcoat,'' ``Voices From a
Locked Room,'' ``The Magnificent Seven'' (1998).
</P>
<P>
   April 4: ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom Menace,'' ``Boys
Don't Cry,'' ``For Love of the Game'' (DVD), ``The Messenger: The
Story of Joan of Arc.'' April 11: ``Thugs.'' April 18: ``Mumford,''
``House on Haunted Hill,'' ``My Date With the President's
Daughter,'' ``End of Days,'' ``That's the Way I Like It,'' ``Love
Kills.'' April 25: ``The Fight Club,'' ``RKO 281,'' ``Iris Blond,''
``Flawless,'' ``Music of the Heart.''
</P>
<P>
   May 2: ``Dogma.'' May 9: ``Bringing Out the Dead.'' May 16:
``The World Is Not Enough'' (DVD).
</P>
</TEXT>
