<P>
   MARDIGRAS _ NEW ORLEANS _ A few things seen around the city this
Mardi Gras season: A cow playing golf. A besotted Grim Reaper. A
cross-dressing cheerleader. Today is Fat Tuesday, the final and
wildest day of a Carnival season that, for residents, started back
in January, on the 12th night after Christmas. It's not just the
tourists and college kids who get wild in the final week of
festivities. (Konigsmark, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SPOLETO-SCFLAG _ Spoleto Festival USA may feel the pinch of an
economic boycott over the state's flag. A top dance company has
already pulled out over the controversy. Will others follow? Are
ticket sales being impacted? How bad will it tarnish the premier
arts event in the southeast? (TSabulis, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
