<HEADER>
A8429 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e BC-TV-PERKINS-COLUMN-TEX     03-06 0362
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-PERKINS-COLUMN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WE'RE NOT SHAKEN OR STIRRED BY `SECRET AGENT'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEN PARISH PERKINS 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Barry Sonnenfeld and Barry Josephson have shrunk their
blockbuster film ``Men in Black'' into ``Secret Agent Man,'' the
new UPN series, but there are no demons and no witty retorts. The
only thing you'll recognize are the black suits worn by the
crimefighters. And even those look like they're straight off the
clearance rack.
</P>
<P>
   Dina Meyer, also in black but with no tie and her shirt
unbuttoned just enough to suggest cleavage, joins Costas Mandylor
and Dondre T. Whitfield as agents working for a top-secret arm of
the government, tracking bad guys with high-tech toys and
high-stakes espionage.
</P>
<P>
   Mandylor is the James Bond type named Monk, and I suppose the
secret agent man referred to in the title. Considered ``the best in
the world,'' he's also a charming, confident ladies' man able to
get himself out of any dangerous mess with the least amount of word
usage.
</P>
<P>
   Meyer is Holiday, ``a skillful agent,'' but she's already
defined by gender. She has the hots for Monk but refuses to let him
in on it, instead tracking his whereabouts from a small room full
of high-tech monitors in the name of protection. Yeah, right. Look
at her face when she sees him locking lips with some women, and
there you have her reasons.
</P>
<P>
   Whitfield is Davis, a gadget mastermind who, at least in
Tuesday's pilot episode, serves as the loyal sidekick.
</P>
<P>
   In some ways, ``Secret Agent Man,'' premiering Tuesday, is
reminiscent of Mandylor's last series, ``Players,'' without the
low-brow fun of seeing rapper Ice T go undercover as a country
singer. Presenting this as a somewhat serious undertaking with
occasional one-liners could be the kiss of death, considering how
difficult it is to mix the two.
</P>
<P>
   Example: A sniper kills his intended victim and cracks, ``Wow.
That musta hurt.''
</P>
<P>
   Oh, boy. Even Will Smith couldn't have saved this.
</P>
<P>
   (Ken Parish Perkins is TV critic for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram .Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the
World Wide Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
