<P>
   CENSUS (Undated) _ In pre-emptive maneuvering over the crucial
matter of political redistricting, a number of Republican states
already have passed laws to prohibit use of census numbers
supplemented by ``sampling.'' With the coming census likely to show
increased percentages of minorities, the issue adds an extra front
to the battle that broke out in Washington after President Clinton
ordered the Census Bureau to produce two sets of numbers _ one
based on a strict head count, the other using sampling to fill in
the gaps created by hard-to-count groups. By KIM COBB.
</P>
