Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms to crack down on ``rogue'' dealers
who sell the highest volume of guns involved in crimes. In Texas
one of those is Bill Carter of Houston, who owns four Carter's
Country gun stores. Carter and other big Texas dealers are outraged
that they are getting blamed for gun violence when they say they
follow all the rules. By JAMES PINKERTON.
</P>
