<P>
   Here are the stories New York Times editors are considering for
the Page 1 of Tuesday, March 7. The N.Y. Times News Service night
supervisor is Pat Ryan; phone: (888) 346-9867; e-mail:
patryan(at)nytimes.com.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-TAIWAN (Beijing) _ In one of the most strident statements
yet on Taiwan, the Chinese military said on Monday that it would
``spare no effort in a blood-soaked battle'' to protect China's
territorial integrity and said that China would not be tricked into
negotiations with Taiwan leaders who secretly oppose rejoining the
motherland. By Erik Eckholm.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   SCOTUS-TANKERS (Washington) _ The Supreme Court rules
unanimously that states cannot set their own, tougher standards for
oil tanker safety, saying this is a duty of federal regulators,
except for rules relating to some unique point of local geography.
By Linda Greenhouse. (800 words)
</P>
