   NEW YORK
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   LOUIMA-TRIAL (New York) _ Three Brooklyn police officers were
convicted on Monday of hatching a plot to cover up the brutal
assault on Abner Louima in a bitterly contested and emotional
verdict that the defendant's lawyers and families vowed through
their tears to fight. The three officers were each found guilty of
conspiring in dozens of telephone calls to obstruct justice by
crafting a false story for the authorities that one of them,
Charles Schwarz, was never involved in the notorious attack three
years ago in the bathroom of a Flatbush station house. By Alan
Feuer.
</P>
