<P>
   OVERTIME-ABUSE _ Here's the flip side of the booming economy:
there's an increase in the number of workers suing their employer
for failure to pay overtime. Atlanta attorney David Worley said
he's filed twice as many overtime lawsuits in the last two years
than in the past. The most recent involves five CVS pharmacists who
allege they've been forced to work 70 hour weeks on a regular basis
without overtime pay. Overtime abuse is occurring in all kinds of
industries, including health care, schools, accounting and even
places like Coca-Cola. A look at this situation. (Joyner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
