Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   COX-RADIO _ Cox Radio enters definitive agreement to buy three
radio stations in Houston and four radio stations in Richmond for
$380 million in cash from Clear Channel Communications. Deal
expected to close in second half. Cox Radio cites demographics of
the markets for its purchases and said the stations to be acquired
not only include ``established market leaders'' but ``start-up and
developing properties with strong upside potential.'' (McNaughton,
Cox News Service). 12.
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-ADS _ Delta is about to launch the first new ad campaign
done by its new agency, Chicago-based Leo Burnett of ``Fly the
Friendly Skies'' fame. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
12.
</P>
<P>
   OVERTIME-ABUSE _ Here's the flip side of the booming economy:
there's an increase in the number of workers suing their employer
for failure to pay overtime. Atlanta attorney David Worley said
he's filed twice as many overtime lawsuits in the last two years
than in the past. The most recent involves five CVS pharmacists who
allege they've been forced to work 70 hour weeks on a regular basis
without overtime pay. Overtime abuse is occurring in all kinds of
industries, including health care, schools, accounting and even
places like Coca-Cola. A look at this situation. (Joyner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   BIZMAGS _ A rundown of the week's financial press. (Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
