<P>
   (Lede story)
</P>
<P>
   MGM-MIRAGE (Undated) _ Mirage Resorts Inc. agreed Monday to be
acquired by MGM Grand Inc. for $4.4 billion in cash, creating a
casino industry powerhouse but probably ending the reign of Stephen
A. Wynn, the founder and chairman of Mirage, as the unofficial king
of Las Vegas. By Andrew Pollack.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic is being sent to NYT graphics clients.
Nonsubscribers can make individual purchase by calling 888-603-1036
or 888-346-9867.)
</P>
<P>
