   LOUIMA-TRIAL (New York) _ Two New York City policemen and one
former officer are convicted of covering up the brutal assault on
Abner Louima, a Haitian immigrant, in an emotional verdict that the
defendants' lawyers and families vow through tears to fight. The
three defendants _ Charles Schwarz, Thomas Wiese and Thomas Bruder
_ each were found guilty in federal District Court in Brooklyn of
