 &UR; ALZA  &LR; _ Alza Corp., the company best known for developing the
nicotine patch, has won government approval to sell a
matchstick-size pump that would be implanted under the skin and
deliver a year's worth of prostate cancer medicine. By Tom Abate
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; PRIVACY  &LR; _ Kevin Manley has no problem giving his name and address
to Web sites like Amazon.com when he needs to buy a book. But
Manley, a Seattle software developer, was stunned to discover
recently that his Sprint PCS cell telephone automatically transmits
his phone number to every Web site he visits using Sprint's new
wireless data service. By Todd Wallack
</P>
