<HEADLINE>
VERONICA COOPER CONVERSE, WIDOW OF GARY COOPER, DIES AT 86 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Veronica Cooper Converse, the widow of the actor Gary
Cooper, died on Feb. 16 at her home in Manhattan. She was 86.
</P>
<P>
   Converse married Cooper in 1933. After his death in 1961, she
married Dr. John Converse, a plastic surgeon, who died in 1981.
</P>
<P>
   Known as Rocky, Cooper was the daughter of a governor of the New
York Stock Exchange; she occasionally worked as an actress.
</P>
<P>
   She was an active fund-raiser for the Institute of
Reconstructive Plastic Surgery at New York University Medical
Center.
</P>
<P>
   In her youth Converse was a noted athlete; she was the
California State Woman's Skeet Champion, as well as a golfer,
swimmer, scuba diver, surfer and tennis player.
</P>
<P>
   She was born in Brooklyn, and is survived by her daughter, Maria
Cooper Janis.  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
